Interface ModelElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Adaptable, EObject, Marked, ModelElement, Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Aim, Alignment, Allocation, Capability, Capacity, Decision, Directory, Document, Domain, Endeavor, Engineer, EngineeredCapability, EngineeredElement, Event, Feature, Forum, Goal, Increment, Issue, IssueCategory, IssuePriority, IssueSeverity, IssueStatus, KeyResult, Link, Message, Module, NamedElement, NamedElementReference, Note, Objective, Organization, Persona, Principle, Product, Release, Topic
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AimImpl, AlignmentImpl, AllocationImpl, CapabilityImpl, CapacityImpl, DecisionImpl, DirectoryImpl, DocumentImpl, DomainImpl, EndeavorImpl, EngineeredCapabilityImpl, EngineeredElementImpl, EngineerImpl, EventImpl, FeatureImpl, ForumImpl, GoalImpl, IncrementImpl, IssueCategoryImpl, IssueImpl, IssuePriorityImpl, IssueSeverityImpl, IssueStatusImpl, KeyResultImpl, LinkImpl, MessageImpl, ModuleImpl, NamedElementReferenceImpl, NoteImpl, ObjectiveImpl, OrganizationImpl, PersonaImpl, PrincipleImpl, ProductImpl, ReleaseImpl, TopicImpl

    public interface ModelElement
extends ModelElement
    A representation of the model object 'Model Element'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Path
    • Resources
    • Documentation
    • Table Of Contents
    • Sections
    • Representations
    See Also:
    EngineeringPackage.getModelElement()

      • getSections

        EList<Document> getSections()
        Returns the value of the 'Sections' containment reference list. The list contents are of type Document. Sections for model element descriptions. In documents sections apply to the document content, i.e. document descriptions cannot have sections. Sections can be nested.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Sections' containment reference list.
        See Also:
        EngineeringPackage.getModelElement_Sections()

      • getRepresentations

        EList<Diagram> getRepresentations()
        Returns the value of the 'Representations' containment reference list. The list contents are of type Diagram. Pluggable representations of a model element, e.g. a component diagram for engineers and modules.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Representations' containment reference list.
        See Also:
        EngineeringPackage.getModelElement_Representations()
